description.narrative: In 2019 UNICEF continued to support Government initiatives towards strengthening the legal and policy framework aimed at better protection of children against violence, abuse and exploitation. The review of the domestic laws was completed, and the process to draft the new Child Law began in both Federal and Kurdistan Region (KRI). At the end of November, the first draft of the law for KRI was shared with key stakeholders for review. The Foster Care Guideline for KRI was endorsed by the Council of Ministers while the assessment of residential care institutions was completed, and the report launched. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:15/01/2019
